    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-05-25T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-05-25T09:00:00-05:00" n="677"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A19/97: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-25T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 25, 1937—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 25—12:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>245. I am deeply impressed by the significance of the Duce’s interview with W. P.
                    Simms reported in my 244, May 25, noon, and I sincerely hope that whatever may
                    develop in regard to the specific question of convoking a conference on the
                    limitation of armaments and any action by the United States in that regard the
                    general principles expressed by the Duce may be given a sympathetic reception
                    not only in the United States but also in England and France. I feel strongly
                    that a rebuff to the Duce at this time might jeopardize a policy of peace and
                    cooperation to which he appears to have committed himself in this statement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
